<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/48889662-olivia"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/48889662-olivia">Olivia</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I read the novella and then dove into the series afterwords, I actually find that it is wayyyyy better as from the start the characters from the start<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I read the novella and then dove into the series afterwords, I actually find that it is wayyyyy better as from the start the characters from the start of the series often make appearances in the later books or are sometimes mentioned. Starting from the top just gave me an entire different experience getting to know each creature from the start of the series to the end.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
