  <span id="freeText12164647591790872251" style="display:none">Weird thing about this book...The world-building was <b> stupidly well done</b>. I would be set for an epic adventure in this world but wrong genre <i>*smirk*</i><br /><br /><b>Wroth</b> is a *new vampire* meaning only a couple of hundred years old, practically a baby compared to the immortal Valkyrie <br /><br />This is honestly what first made me pick up the book with Valkryie being the unique magic addition that I was curious how this author would incorporate into her story <br /><br />And by the GODS it paid off! <br /><br />The <i>Valkyrie</i> coven? group? sorority? Were fucking amazing with their unique origin story, each with their own specialized powers, and <b>general mission in life to fuck people up</b> <br /><br /><b>
