        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer300376003" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer414369568556952376">As they appear in the series from time to time, I was always curious about the love story of the dangerously charming Nikolai Wroth and the fabulously beautiful Myst. Nikolai is one of the Wroth brothers. Myst is a Valkyrie, and she is not only beautiful but a fierce warrior as well. <br/><br/>If I say that reading their novella made me disappointed, it would not express the intensity of my disillusionment. <br/><br/>Nikolai’s sense of humor, expressed in figures, nears to zero. For the most part of the story, he b</span>
  <span id="freeText414369568556952376" style="display:none">As they appear in the series from time to time, I was always curious about the love story of the dangerously charming Nikolai Wroth and the fabulously beautiful Myst. Nikolai is one of the Wroth brothers. Myst is a Valkyrie, and she is not only beautiful but a fierce warrior as well. <br /><br />If I say that reading their novella made me disappointed, it would not express the intensity of my disillusionment. <br /><br />Nikolai’s sense of humor, expressed in figures, nears to zero. For the most part of the story, he behaves like a possessive, overbearing jerk.<br /><br />Myst’s life mission, as it turns out, is fighting with vampires. Plus, she has an Xbox addiction, and loves painting her nails. <br /><br />What makes them fall in love with each other remains a mystery. Their relationship is forced, lacks romance, honesty, and intimacy. I hate the whole idea on which Nikolai and Myst’s relationship is built. The erotic scenes are repulsive, and too many for a 160-page novella. There is no considerable plot, action, or humor. Furthermore, Nikolai’s <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[pseudo self-sacrifice  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> at the end of the story is totally irritating.<br /><br />I have no intention to give up the series, but it is a novella I should have missed for the sake of my peace of mind.<br /><br /></span>
