              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16078143-rachel-annie?shelf=paranormal-uf-romance">paranormal-uf-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1037791549" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6562819114589055665">I was rather surprised at how much I enjoyed this one. The whole tough-as-nails immortal heroine usually puts me off, but I liked Myst. And the whole dubious consent thing? I can&apos;t believe I&apos;m saying this, but it was acceptable here.<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1391348815ra/8376630.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Ugh, I dunno. It&apos;s complicated...<br/><br/>But, I like Ms. Cole&apos;s writing style; despite this being just a novella, the content made it feel slightly <i>epic</i> at times. Though I could have done without the &quot;Wroth has a giant schlong&quot; subplot. <br/><br/>Myst is an f&apos;ing Valkyrie. She can han</span>
  <span id="freeText6562819114589055665" style="display:none">I was rather surprised at how much I enjoyed this one. The whole tough-as-nails immortal heroine usually puts me off, but I liked Myst. And the whole dubious consent thing? I can't believe I'm saying this, but it was acceptable here.<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1391348815ra/8376630.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Ugh, I dunno. It's complicated...<br><br>But, I like Ms. Cole's writing style; despite this being just a novella, the content made it feel slightly <i>epic</i> at times. Though I could have done without the "Wroth has a giant schlong" subplot. <br><br>Myst is an f'ing Valkyrie. She can handle it. ☺</span>
  <a data-text-id="6562819114589055665" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


